{"id":76747,"date":"2021-11-01T06:47:30","date_gmt":"2021-11-01T13:47:30","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/?p=76747"},"modified":"2021-11-01T06:47:30","modified_gmt":"2021-11-01T13:47:30","slug":"linkedin-learning-academic-credit","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/linkedin-learning-academic-credit\/","title":{"rendered":"LinkedIn Learning Offers a Path to Academic Credit, But it&#8217;s Complicated"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As of recently, you can earn academic credit via <a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/provider\/linkedin-learning\">LinkedIn Learning<\/a>. In short, some of their Learning Paths can be applied toward certain qualifications at some partner universities. The system is similar to <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/list-of-mooc-based-microcredentials\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">edX\u2019s MicroMasters or Coursera\u2019s MasterTrack<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. But looking at the fine print, there are some important differences. Here\u2019s how LinkedIn Learning\u2019s credit system works.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Learning Paths<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">LinkedIn Learning\u2019s credit system starts with their Learning Paths. These are curated lists of courses geared toward a certain skill or job \u2014 for instance, <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/learning\/paths\/become-a-graphic-designer?u=2163426\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Become a Graphic Designer<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. To enroll in a path, you must subscribe to LinkedIn Learning ($30 a month or $240 a year). But as Class Central noted in a previous article, <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/linkedin-learning-free-learning-paths\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">some LinkedIn Learning Paths are free<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Currently, LinkedIn Learning offers over 500 Learning Paths. However, <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/learning\/search?entityType=LEARNING_PATH&amp;software=Academic%20Credits&amp;u=2163426\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">only ~40 of them<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (most in English), can lead to academic credit. And this modality is limited to LinkedIn Learning\u2019s university partners, and to specific qualifications within those universities.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">University Partners<\/span><\/h2>\n<figure id=\"attachment_76749\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-76749\" style=\"width: 1024px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/linkedin-learning-credit-partners.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-full wp-image-76749\" src=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/linkedin-learning-credit-partners.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"512\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/linkedin-learning-credit-partners.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/linkedin-learning-credit-partners-300x150.png 300w, https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/linkedin-learning-credit-partners-768x384.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-76749\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">LinkedIn Learning First Credit Partners<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For now, LinkedIn Learning has partnered with <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/members.linkedin.com\/en-gb\/academic-credit#partner-profiles\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">seven academic institutions<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> worldwide. Each of these institutions has endorsed certain Learning Paths, meaning that these can count toward some of the qualifications offered by the university, chiefly some of their degree programs.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For example, the University of Northumbria, UK, has endorsed the <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/learning\/paths\/become-a-data-scientist\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Become a Data Scientist<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/learning\/paths\/become-a-data-analyst\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Become a Data Analyst<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> paths: these can count toward the university master\u2019s degree in data science as equivalent to <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.northumbria.ac.uk\/study-at-northumbria\/courses\/data-science-msc-dtfdsc6\/linkedin-learning\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">20 of the degree\u2019s 180 credits<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. But there are some caveats.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Caveats &amp; Competition<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So far, the credit system we\u2019ve described closely resembles <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/list-of-mooc-based-microcredentials\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">edX\u2019s MicroMasters and Coursera\u2019s MasterTracks<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. And the similarities don\u2019t stop here. Most notably, completing a Learning Path doesn&#8217;t guarantee acceptance into the corresponding degree at the endorsing university: while they might help you get accepted, you still need to apply to the university like anyone else.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But herein also lies a difference. Unlike with MicroMasters, to use a Learning Path toward a degree, finishing the path isn&#8217;t enough. You also have to <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/help\/learning\/answer\/123518\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">complete an assignment<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> to validate your learning. For instance, the University of Huddersfield, UK, asks for a <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.hud.ac.uk\/postgraduate\/linkedin-learning-pathways\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2500-word report<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> demonstrating your knowledge and readiness for their degrees. The University of South Australia will even ask you to <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/online.unisa.edu.au\/linkedin-learning\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">pay $125 to take their online assessment<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So it\u2019s only after <\/span><b>(1)<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> completing the Learning Path, <\/span><b>(2)<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> completing the corresponding (sometimes paid) assessment, and finally <\/span><b>(3)<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> being accepted into the corresponding university and degree program that you\u2019ll effectively be able to earn academic credit through LinkedIn Learning.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Note that it\u2019s only after spending effort completing <\/span><b>(1)<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and <\/span><b>(2)<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, that you\u2019ll find out about <\/span><b>(3)<\/b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, since you\u2019ll need to submit your path certificate and assignment when you apply to the university. This isn\u2019t too different from <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/us-accreditations\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">credit transfer in traditional universities<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: you typically only apply for credit transfer after acceptance. But if you\u2019re rejected, you can try to take your credit elsewhere.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With LinkedIn Learning Paths, by contrast, credit is conditional: it\u2019s tied to a specific institution and program. So if you\u2019re rejected, you might find yourself with a certificate you don\u2019t need and an assessment you can\u2019t use. Your only option to earn academic credit might be to reapply.<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>LinkedIn Learning credit system resembles edX&#8217;s MicroMasters, but there are some important differences.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":88,"featured_media":76750,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[103],"tags":[347],"acf":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO Premium plugin v18.3 (Yoast SEO v18.5.1) - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>LinkedIn Learning Offers a Path to Academic Credit, But it&#039;s Complicated \u2014 Class Central<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"LinkedIn Learning credit system resembles edX&#039;s MicroMasters, but there are some important differences.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/linkedin-learning-academic-credit\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"LinkedIn Learning Offers a Path to Academic Credit, But it&#039;s Complicated\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"LinkedIn Learning credit system resembles edX&#039;s MicroMasters, but there are some important differences.\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https:\/\/www.classcentral.com\/report\/linkedin-learning-academic-credit\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"The Report by Class